		<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    The Wizards Guide</b></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><A href="mailto:">Auxantaur</a> | 
		            6/8/1999 5:39:25 PM</b></font></p>
		         <a href="guides.asp">
		         <font face="verdana" size="2">Return to guide listing.</font></a>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">****FAQ located at the bottom*****<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
AUXANTAUR'S GUIDE TO WIZARD COMBAT AND TACTICS.<BR>
<BR>
So you are a low/medium lvl wizard and are complaining how bad off you are and how often you die right?<BR>
<BR>
Don't sweat my friend. Its not the character, its the tactics.. BELIEVE ME.<BR>
<BR>
In ALL modesty (i am trying to give tactics, not beat my chest) in 5 days i haven't died; that's 5 days of playing at LEAST 6 hours at a sitting. This is common. I am now lvl 20+ , and the people i started out with are no higher than i am, often lower.<BR>
<BR>
You want to know why?, because i think like a wizard .. my whole party can get slaughtered 3 or 4 times, and i walk out alive every time. No, i don't run at the first sign of trouble, no i DONT wait and withhold my spells watching my party slowly get annihilated, AND/OR waiting to see if its possible they could win, and if not i leave them to die (unlike many wizards i have seen).<BR>
<BR>
Here's the secret; YOU must be in charge of battle tactics, now i know it sounds totally ridiculous, but i am living proof to the success of this. Heres how you do it:<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
1. <BR>
Create 4 hot keys, converting a few of your buttons in the social section. (if you don't know how to do this, ask someone)<BR>
Button 1 should say HELP me out here!!!<BR>
Button 2 should say LOW on MANA<BR>
Button 3 should say RETREATING ( not RETREAT, but retretING; this is to inform your party, its not an order for your party)<BR>
Button 4 should be an 'assist' button<BR>
<BR>
these are self explanatory. The third button gives your party suitable warning that you can no longer continue the battle and are going to zone; they wont blame you; all good players know that a wizard without mana is useless against major creatures. If the situation presents itself that the creature(s) isnt doing alot of damage to your party, then MED there on the spot and tell your party what you are doing.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
2. (general rule - applies always)<BR>
<BR>
When attacking creatures with spells only attack the ones that are currently being attacked by one of your party.. and DO NOT open up with a volley of your strongest spells, this will only bring the creature straight to you. If you feel confident enough that you can root it, then kill it with your strongest spells before it closes on you, do it; just root it again regularly so it stays PUT. If not, open up with some mid damage ones first .. soften it up and give your tanks time to cause it damage, to make it less likely that it will come after you. When it is nearly dead<BR>
and you can kill it with one spell, do it, you save your tanks valuable seconds, so they can help out others in your party much faster.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
3.<BR>
<BR>
When you join the group, or when new members arrive, inform your party that when you are out of mana, you will either zone or fight hand to hand or sit and med depending on the status of the battle; they will understand and appreciate your candidness. Tell them what to attack (by creature type or name type) first. IF the members bitch about you giving orders, be diplomatic and say that to be successful the wizard has to know where to put his efforts...it shuts them up. <BR>
This will assist you in knowing where to use your spells. Now in a large group of the same type monster, its impossible to tell who is fighting what; use the assist button you made; target the tank of the group and then hit it; it will the target the foe he/she is fighting. Do not engage hand to hand at this point. The first thing you do is root the target, if it fails, root it again until it works; then blast it with several weaker spells. By the time the root wears off, the tank would have got its attention back :)) .....By now you should be down to about half mana, give or take depending on your level. If you are fighting multiple creatures; then target another of of your party, and see what he/she is fighting... if you see one of the creatures low enough that you can kill it with 1 or 2 of your mightiest spells Do IT, even if this burns 90% of your mana. With that creature down, your fellow members can gang up on the rest. Use your &quot;low of mana&quot; hotkey now; its courtesy to inform your party that you will be unable to cause serious damage any more.<BR>
Ok if all has gone well you have full health and a little mana left; its not much, but it's something. <BR>
<BR>
4.<BR>
<BR>
Hand to Hand<BR>
<BR>
This is judgement time. Based on how good you are at this you will either live or die. <BR>
<BR>
Scenario &quot;A&quot;<BR>
If the members of your party are losing really BADLY,not just one but all, push your 'retreating' hot key button and LEAVE. Remember you are probably the only one not engaged in hand-to-hand at this point. Often this will force your whole party to retreat, which may be a good or bad thing. There is nothing more you can do, remember a warrior has many more HP then you and far better armour.. you get involved and do any notable damage that creature will KILL YOU. Especially if you are down to half hit points, it will smell blood, and taunting a creature off you then seldom works. Using the hotkey button you made, tell them you are retreating, move away some distance and suggest they retreat; do NOT make it an order, like &quot;RUN&quot;. If they remain fighting you LEAVE, don't stand there and watch, you goto the zone and ZONE; this isn't a spectator sport.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Scenario &quot;B&quot;<BR>
If it looks 50/50 ask the healers for a mana status, remember currently YOU are the only one not engaged in combat, the rest are too busy to do the things you have the precious few seconds to do. If the report is bad....depending on your personal courage and skill this is what you do. Find the weakest creature that is being attacked by one of your party ( not just one that is fighting your party but not being currently attacked..this is VERY important, and use your assist key to be sure ), one with the lowest HP and engage it. <BR>
Sometimes it may never even look your direction and you can slug it out with no danger to yourself. IF the creature turns to you, back off a few feet. IF it follows, stop and continue fighting, and refer to scenario C. IF it turns to you and you back off, but it doesn't follow and instead goes back to attacking one of your group; this is where the fun starts.... You dart in there, but don't attack, it will turn to you, IMMEDIATELY back off out of its hit range, then dart back in there again; do it again and again and again. Those precious few seconds when its trying to hit you are seconds when members of your party are hitting IT, and they themselves are not getting hurt. Continue to do this and the monster will die without ever touching your party again. It may annoy party members, but it WORKS, and an annoyance is better than death. You may get hit a few times but you'll live. If at anytime the monster follows , stop and fight it, and do what i suggest in scenario C.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Scenario &quot;C&quot;<BR>
 If it looks 50/50, ask the healers for a mana status. If the replie(s) are good, then you may engage the weakest enemy; first use the assist button to find out which is the weakest enemy by clicking on the group members at the top right of the screen, then hitting your assist button. Engage that creature. <BR>
If it turns to face you, do not back off; keep fighting and when you get down to three bubbles, hit your 'help me out here' hotkey 2 or 3 times... if not help is forthcoming and you are down to 2 bubbles, use your remaining mana to root the creature, then the 'retreating' hotkey then you ZONE. If it fails, or you are stunned or you are down to 1 bubble, don't bother running; die like a man/woman. Running only makes it harder for your group to attack the creature, and it splits your group making it more likely that others will die.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Scenario &quot;D&quot;<BR>
If it looks like your group will win this one, sit and med; DONT med next to the battle, med closer to the zone, but keep a visual line on your party, every 20 seconds get up and have a look how they are going; if its bad; ZONE, if good, keep medding. When you have about 2 bubbles, get up and blast the creature that is attacking your most injured group member; remember they smell blood so it is unlikely they will come after you. If they do remember to leave enough to root them, then ZONE. <BR>
At this point you may engage the enemy freely hand to hand, have fun! you will be looked on favourably if you slug it out with them.<BR>
<BR>
VICTORY!<BR>
<BR>
Who says a wizard is only as good as his spells? not I :)<BR>
<BR>
Auxantaur; High Elf Wizard Guild member of The House Of Light<BR>
Bristlebain server<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
FAQ  SECTION<BR>
<BR>
Q. How do I create these hotkeys?<BR>
A. ok&#8230;if you hit the F10 key a few times, your window will change to show your interface area, the one which allows you to open your spell book, and goto the social or combat menu etc. Click on the social button. This section contains many useless functions, like telling you the length of time you have been in-game. Right click on one of these, and a dialog box will open up. If you are creating e.g. the 'help me out' button; rename the actual name of the button  (delete the current contents) and call it help. In the area bellow, delete all text , and replace it with  /group HELP me out here!!!!  Close the dialog box. On the bottom left of the interface screen is your hot key options, using the arrows, scroll until you get to a blank one. Left click and hold down on this modified button and drag it to a slot in the hotkey area.. Carefully position this button over the slot and left click to drop it into place. This may not work first time, so try again. Now repeat this procedure for the rest.<BR>
<BR>
Q. What if my group has more than one mage? What's the strategy then?<BR>
A. It DOESN'T MATTER. You do what you have to do and let that mage do his/her thing .. if he/she helps you kill the creature, fine. If he/she stuffs it and gets killed.. refer him/her to my post :)<BR>
<BR>
Q. My team keeps ordering me around and I cant do what you suggest! What should I do?<BR>
A. If you regularly group with these people; wait till you all die; then politely suggest that you be allowed the freedom to put your efforts where you see they are needed. Even the most thick headed individual will quickly catch on.. Your group is important, but so are you. If they are people you just met, kindly explain that you are a wizard and you know what a wizard has to do; that you best know what tactics to use because YOU have to use them ; a ranger may not have a clue how a wizard should fight, and probably is only guessing; remember this and be diplomatic about it.<BR>
<BR>
Q. My root fails 80% of the time and the creature kills me! What do I do?<BR>
A. Most likely your skill in the school that uses root is low. If you are getting fizzles, go and do some fishing for a hour; while you fish, continuously cast root on yourself to improve your skill. If you are not getting fizzes, but the root was resisted; it means the creature is powerful and your chance of rooting it is not good. Here is what I have observed .. the more damaged the creature is, the easier it is for it to be affected by spells &#8230;. Hit the creature with some mid strength spells while your tanks hammer it out. When it weakens try it then, you will find you have greater success. Also the higher in level you go the more effective root is .. I can regularly root creatures which conn yellow or red; patience and practice.  <BR>
<BR>
Q. Sometimes I cast spells and the whole enemy group comes after me and kills me! Why?!<BR>
A. Firstly, are you using AE (area effect) spells? If so, DON'T , in fact don't even buy them &#8230; I havent used one for 5 levels because they are totally crappo; blame it on the game designers. Only use the 'shock' type of spells, or things like firebolt, or lightning bolt; spells which only target one creature at a time. Tip: Make sure you have a DIRECT line of sight between you and the target for the bolt spells, nothing can be in the way or you will loose the mana, and it wont even hit your target.<BR>
Secondly refer to point 2 in my notes of how not to make yourself a target.<BR>
<BR>
Q. I always seem to get rooted my shamans, and then they kill me! What do I do?<BR>
A. The first chance you get, buy an item that increases your resistance to magic, the more the better; if you do this you will find there spells will fail more often.<BR>
If the creature has targeted you in the first place, then you weren't doing your job, if it roots you it should already be rooted BY you, so it cant kill you because you are not close enough to it. The tanks should finish it off before it gets to attack you.<BR>
<BR>
Q. I never seem to have enough mana when I need it, and my party dies because I didn't have enough mana, what can I do?<BR>
A. :)&#8230;&#8230;. It isn't your fault your mana supply is limited, that's how the game is designed. If you are very new, you may consider making a new character and putting as many points as you can into intelligence; for that little bit xtra mana..<BR>
The trick is to manage the mana you have; use your spells like a surgeons scalpel; quick and precise&#8230;don't burn your mana if you don't have to, look for an opening, the right time, the right monster and STRIKE. Don't feel bad if for most of the battle you aren't casting; that's not your job. Many low level players don't want wizards and I don't blame them .. we are awfully weak to begin with; but perceiver and you will soon become (along with clerics) the most desirable party member.<BR>
<BR>
Q Your guide isn't working, none of this applies in the game, things are too random, so what else do you suggest? <BR>
A. This is a GUIDE &#8230; treat it as such, in time you will be able to fine tune these tactics to your own personal taste; beyond this I have no suggestions except that this is how I do it&#8230;..take it from someone who knows what he is talking about.<BR>
<BR>

			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
